Hereâ€™s how to Deadlift with proper form:
- 
Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell
- 
Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip
- 
Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar
- 
Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back
- 
Take a big breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight
- 
Hold the weight for a second at the top, with locked hips and knees. Then return the weight to the floor by moving your hips back while bending your legs. Rest a second at the bottom and repeat.
- 
Your lower back must stay neutral to avoid injury. Rounding it during heavy DeadliftsÂ is dangerousÂ for your spine. It puts uneven pressure on your spinal discs which can injure them.
- 
Always Deadlift with a neutral lower back â€“ maintain the natural inward curve ofÂ your lower spine.
- 
The fastest way to increase your Deadlift is to improve your form. By pulling more efficiently, you can use more muscles and Deadlift heavier weights. This results in more strength andÂ muscle gains.
- 
The best way to improve your form is by practicing DeadliftsÂ with proper form.
- 
