One day you finally knew
What you had to do, and began, Though the voices around you Kept shouting
Their bad adviceâ€š
Though the whole house
Began to tremble
And you felt the old tug
At your ankles.
â€œMend my life!â€
Each voice cried.
But you didnâ€™t stop.
You knew what you had to do, Though the wind pried
With its stiff fingers
At the very foundationsâ€š
Though their melancholy
Was terrible.
It was already late
Enough, and a wild night,
And the road full of fallen Branches and stones.
But little by little,
As you left their voices behind, The stars began to burn Through the sheets of clouds, And there was a new voice, Which you slowly
Recognized as your own,
That kept you company
As you strode deeper and deeper Into the world,
Determined to do
The only thing you could doâ€š Determined to save
The only life you could save
.
-
Mary Oliver
