The reason you would pair up a routine like this is because the muscles that are responsible for â€œpushingâ€ or â€œpullingâ€ essentially work in sync with one another. For instance, a bench press incorporates your pecs, shoulders, and triceps all in one movement. SO - since these muscles are all working together on a large portion of your lifts, it only make sense to pair them together when training. By doing so, your workouts will be more effective and efficient.
